t researcher recruitment all jointuse research institutes medical care medical tourism medical partnering you are here home  products fiber  apparel  wacoal women’s intimate apparel products fiber  apparel wacoal women’s intimate apparel outline wacoal is a company with a clear mission to create new value that exceeds the expectations of each generation of consumers much of the diverse lineup of women’s intimate apparel readily available in japan today would not have been possible without the determination of wacoal to create solutions to consumer need bras designed to enhance the beauty of woman a concept quite different to any product that had come before a pioneering girdle the patent for which was the first international patent ever obtained in japan high performance underwear inspired by shipbuilding technology and manufactured in three dimensions using a d model luxury high quality lingerie created using the world’s most outstanding fiber technologies wacoal has a long history of excellence in its products of using highlevel technology to create highquality products today wacoal is in the process of strengthening its reputation and appeal in the global underwear market“making women beautiful” the mission statement of wacoal’s founderin  koichi tsukamoto who was the founder of wako shoji a company involved in the wholesale and retail of women’s accessories and general items somehow discovered that american women wore inside their clothes an item known as a “bra pad” he started work on developing his own version of the brasserie and in  he had succeeded in the same year he developed an ambitious fivestage fiftyyear plan to become the leading manufacturer of women’s underwear in the world according to his plan by  when the plan entered its fifth stage or decade wacoal would be a significant presence on the international underwear market his truly determined plan carved out a vision for the company to be a major player on a global industrial stage despite japan still suffering in the aftermath of the second world war today over  years after the company was established wacoal operates in  countries worldwide and has indeed become the international powerhouse that tsukamoto envisioned boosting wacoal’s global successin  wacoal established a product research division and began to address the issues of intimate apparel design from a human engineering perspective measuring and analyzing the true physical shape of japanese women that department still exists today although now it is known as the human science research center the center carries out research on many aspects of the female body going beyond just body shape and external beauty and focusing also on quantifying the other experiences associated with wearing underwear such as the way a fabric feels against the body and the fit and comfort of the garment every year the center collects data from a group of women totaling between  and  from a wide demographic range from late teens to women in their sixties the data accumulated over the past forty years has now reached more than  individual entries this allows product development to be built on a basis of strong scientific evidence it allows wacoal to develop items that are unaffected by fleeting fashion or trends and concentrate instead on the things that women truly need wacoal’s measurements are made using a number of different machines and scales and the technology that enables this accuracy in measurement is vital to wacoal’s success when the company was first established measurements were made of women’s bodies in  body parts in total using the same method to determine physical size as was used in schools this simple method continues to be used today and it has been central to the accumulation of vast accurate data in the s the company introduced a threedimensional measuring device allowing researchers to display and archive information in threedimensions on the threedimensions of the actual human body in addition wacoal worked with osaka university to develop a twodimensional silhouette analysis device capable of obtaining data on human silhouettes the device is then able to display the average silhouette for women in each age range and this information is also used in store in the same way that contour lines are used to indicate the undulations of mountains on a map moiré fringe analysis is a technique used to express the curves and bumps of the human body twodimensionally this analysis is another core technology that helps to shape product development at wacoal the human science research center then uses the data to develop diverse brands for different generations body shapes and purposes today wacoal has a lineup of over  brands including lines other than women’s intimate apparel through which it strives to answer the needs of diverse women customers a facility similar to the human science research center in japan has now been established in china and the usa and local researchers are beginning to build up new databases on the figures of women customers in those locations the wacoal sports science corporation located in the usa has conducted research on the mechanisms of joints and muscles on more than  subjects and has used the findings of that research to obtain more than  patents worldwide with a strong focus on basic research and a design and manufacturing approach based on objective data these achievements are all characteristic of wacoal’s proven ability to continuously create new value towards the next generationtoday wacoal refers to this business field as the ‘body designing business’ and it is dedicated to moving forward in this area the ‘body’ referred to here is both the physical body and the body of emotions that makes up every human wacoal attempts to provide value in the form of beauty comfort and health to this dual body this philosophy is about more than just conventional underwear it has been extended for example to wacoal’s high performance wear brand cwx designed to enhance physical condition during sports it has also been applied to development of inner wear ranges such as fitness walker and cross walker® aiming to improve walking posture cross walker® was launched in spring  and recorded an incredible  million unit sales between launch and the end of  cross walker shakitto® an improved version of the line sold  units in the five months immediately following its  launch when the shakitto® line of tops was tested on  subjects around  of all wearers recorded improved posture after wearing wacoal also has several prominent brand ambassadors including major league baseball player ichiro suzuki and professional tennis player ai sugiyama who testify to the benefits of wacoal’s sports lines wacoal is expected to continue its positive performance in sports markets according to an analysis by a company that provides online information about the global apparel and textile industries women will on average purchase bras at a rate of around two a year even when they already own five or more another survey carried out in  by a japanese marketing company indicated that of the  million women in china only  million wear bras leaving around  million chinese women who have yet to begin habitually wearing bras put very simply this suggests that the potential market for bras in china is several times over that of japan emerging markets such as china represent a very exciting opportunity for the women’s underwear market and are likely to provoke severe competition in the future intimate apparel used to be considered little more than something that was worn under clothes making functionality — support correction and comfort — much more important than design today however the design and image of products are also of crucial importance and there are some truly unique and surprisingly bold designs available on the market in japan wacoal commands the largest share of the women’s underwear market but nonjapanese brands such as triumph international are chasing the second largest share with large american underwear brand victoria’s secret and french lingerie company chantelle highly popular in france and italy also as strong competitors the popularity of these brands is a clear indication of consumer demand for sensual and luxurious design in addition to functional performance as underwear faced with this global underwear market and its evolving demands wacoal will continue to create new value and continue to achieve corporate growth by looking at objective data that has been carefully accumulated over extended periods developing products based on the findings of research on the human body and applying top level manufacturing technology to promote the further advancement of intimate apparel jul  about the authorhiromi jitsukata is a reporter for japanest nippon httpwwwwacoalholdingsjpindexehtml（　wacoal holdings corp　） how to use my page click here for instructions on japanest nippon my page contact │ privacy policy │ terms of service │ about us copyright   japanest nippon all rights reserved  toggle navigation jake                x  btemptd  trefle  dadado  une nana cool   peach john                               free up owow girl activity  more      physical activity  more      wow girl  recommend item   【】 be  【】iearth  de   【】up  bd x 【x】v de   【】 bc   【】   d   【】  aa   【】 de  movie  more wow girl  brands  knowledge  more     check ，     ，             ！   ！               salute  facekbook   faq   taiwan wacoal co ltd all rights reserved corporate strategy  wacoal holdings corp wacoal global site japanese wacoal as a manufacturer what only wacoal can do corporate  group information csr to our shareholders home   to our shareholders   corporate strategy corporate strategy outline of mediumterm management plan for the period from fy  to march  the wacoal group has created a vision of the future establish a stronger global presence for the wacoal group in our threeyear mediumterm management plan starting from april  in order to achieve that management resources and group networks need to be effectively used to the maximum extent and we always continue supplying cuttingedge products opening up new markets in the field of underwear culture and earning the trust of customers around the world in addition we will enter fields where we have a competitive advantage as well as new areas of business with the aim of increasing our enterprise value still further the earnings targets for the threeyear mediumterm management plan are net sales of over  billion yen and operating income of more than  billion yen reflection on the previous mediumterm management plan business environment of the group and risks reflection on the previous mediumterm management plan under the previous mediumterm management plan in order to achieve net sales of over  billion yen operating income of  billion yen and operating margin of over  we worked to expand the points of contact with customers in domestic business win area share and increase sales and earnings in overseas business in china the us and europe markets based on our five values of reconfirm and implement management philosophy evolve into global company strengthen groups comprehensive capabilities through coordination with companies inside and outside of japan strengthen profit structure to be able to respond to environmental change and build mutual trust with society the results of these initiatives in relation to sales in japan did not result in significant growth in earning in existing business lines however earnings increased when ai co ltd whose main business line is our new entry into the swimsuit market was included in overseas business in addition to the effects of weakening yen actual growth was achieved even in the local currency base and sales have likewise grown by a wide margin however revenue for peach john and other businesses ultimately fell on the profit side we took positive measures to reduce costs such as the aggregation of materials procurement and shifting production to the asean region this helped us to respond effectively to the weakening yen and increase in manufacturing costs however operating margin of  ultimately fell slightly short of the target business environment of the group and risks within japan real disposable income remains stagnant however consumer consciousness of saving money has increased even more and future trends in individual consumption continue to be unclear in addition the closure of commercial facilities continues and the commercial environment surrounding the ladies innerwear market in japan has become more stringent on the other hand new market opportunities are being created by developments such as the increase of inbound consumption and the rise of new distribution channels advancement in womens social status and the broadening of their role and the holding of the  tokyo olympics overseas although there are many causes of risk such as the stalling of the chinese economy and economic and political instability in the european area overseas business has been the largest engine of growth in the group and this fact has not changed accurately grasping the social environment and consumer needs of each country and region and developing products and marketing strategies that put down roots in the local area is essential by increasing our brand value in the us strengthening management structures in european business and working towards even greater profitability in the business of china we will building solid management foundations to maintain a high profitability structure in the worlds three major markets while expanding sales in emerging regions also with wage rises in asian countries and risks related to the procurement of raw materials the business environment of the manufacturing sector gets more and more difficult every year we will expand the global supply chain and strengthen internal group cooperation in order to increase the global competitiveness of our products and ensure a stable supply page top secure earnings in domestic business we will construct a customerfocused channel mix based on the assumption of continuous development of new high valueadded products in order to achieve this we first work on increasing the productivity of our wholesale operations and improving the profitability of our retail business next we intend to work on revising our trading systems and integrating our it systems in order to improve our customer base and enable mutual referral of customers between channels priority measures of wacoal business domestic wacoal corp fiscal  numerical targets net sales ¥ billion up  versus fiscal  fiscal  ¥ million operating income ¥ billion down  versus fiscal  fiscal  ¥ million increasing productivity of our wholesale business through expansion of the area sales system increasing profitability of our direct sales business through expansion of physical stores and reduction of costs building a channel mix from a customer viewpoint for mutual referral of customers between our ecommerce site and network of direct sales stores net sales  operating income wacoal corp ai co ltd fiscal  numerical targets net sales ¥ billion up  versus fiscal  fiscal  ¥ million operating income ¥ billion up  versus fiscal  fiscal  ¥ million strengthening of stores which open all year round and expansion of resort wear products joint development of swimwear by group subsidiaries and sales expansion around mutual expansion of products net sales  operating income ai co ltd page top generate further growth in overseas business in order to respond effectively to the changing external environments of individual countries and regions we will work hard on constructing a solid management infrastructure in the following three markets the us europe and china we also work on increasing the added value of our products as well as strengthening our internal systems priority measures of wacoal business overseas wacoal international corpusa